-hand information about the linguistic habits of Siwan women, an aspect which is generally difficult to access in this gender-segregated community. The book sheds light on Berber-Arabic contact at the core of the Arab world and at a critical time when individual linguistic repertoires are expanding and Arabic is emerging as a powerful resource.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aArabisch. 4aBerber. 4aMehrsprachigkeit. 4aMinderheitensprachen. 4aSiwa Oasis (Ägypten). 4aSoziolinguistischer Wandel. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aArabic.  aBerber.  aMinority languages.  aMultilingualism.  aSiwa Oasis (Egypt).  aSociolinguistic Change.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311133219208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2024z97831114380470 cEPUBz97831110465180 cprintz978311104512240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311104535140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111045351423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111045351/original  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  a978-3-11-143804-7  De Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2024b2024  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles